- Please make sure that all the modules are following the standard and if there are any modules which are not following the standard, please update them to follow the standard. This includes ensuring that each module has the required configuration files, adheres to naming conventions, and maintains consistency in structure and documentation.
- Please ensure that all the modules are properly documented, including their functionalities, configurations, and any dependencies they may have. This documentation should be clear and accessible to developers who will be working with the modules, and it should be kept up to date as changes are made.
- Please review the current implementation of the modules to ensure that they are aligned with the design principles outlined in the Nodics framework. This includes verifying that capabilities are respected, implementations are negotiable, and that the layered module hierarchy is maintained. Any deviations from these principles should be addressed and corrected to ensure that the system remains customizable and maintainable without modifying the core framework.
- Please conduct a thorough review of the test coverage for each module, ensuring that all critical functionalities are adequately tested and that the tests are aligned with the design principles of the Nodics framework. This includes verifying that tests respect the layered module hierarchy, that they cover multi-tenancy and modular deployment scenarios, and that they provide traceability and backward compatibility. Any gaps in test coverage should be identified and addressed to ensure that the system remains robust and reliable.
